# Database Configuration
# =====================
# Neon PostgreSQL connection string (use pooled connection with -pooler suffix)
# Format: postgresql://USER:PASSWORD@HOST-pooler.REGION.aws.neon.tech/DATABASE?sslmode=require
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://username:password@ep-xxxx-pooler.us-east-1.aws.neon.tech/dbname?sslmode=require"

# NextAuth.js Configuration
# =========================
# Secret key for JWT encryption (generate with: openssl rand -base64 32)
NEXTAUTH_SECRET="your-random-secret-key-here-use-openssl-rand-base64-32"

# Application URL (change for production)
NEXTAUTH_URL="http://localhost:3000"

# Notes:
# ------
# 1. DATABASE_URL: Must use Neon's pooled connection string (with -pooler) for serverless deployments
# 2. NEXTAUTH_SECRET: Generate a secure random string for production
# 3. NEXTAUTH_URL: Update to your production domain when deploying (e.g., https://your-app.vercel.app)
#
# For local development, copy this file to .env and replace the placeholder values with your actual credentials.
